intro: Taonabo patens, commonly known as the spreading taonabo, is a flowering plant native to certain regions of Southeast Asia. It belongs to the family Araliaceae and is characterized by its woody stems and compound leaves. The plant produces small, clustered white flowers that are typically borne on inflorescences. It thrives in moist, shaded environments and is often found in tropical forests. Its botanical features make it an interesting subject for both ecological studies and horticultural cultivation.
